                <h1>Milton Hershey: A Sweet Timeline of Chocolate Innovation</h1>
                <p>Milton Hershey (1857-1945) was a pioneer in the American chocolate industry. In 1900, he established the Hershey Chocolate Company, revolutionizing the production of chocolate with milk. In 1907, the iconic Hershey's Kisses were introduced. He also founded the town of Hershey, Pennsylvania, and established a school for underprivileged children.</p>
